Task: Write an email to my team informing them that our Q3 roadmap is delayed by 3 weeks due to a vendor delay.

Context:
- The delay is caused by an external vendor issue.
- The audience is my internal team who needs clear, professional communication.
- The tone should be professional but approachable—neither too corporate nor stiff.
- I have a mitigation plan in progress but the details are not finalized yet.
- The team needs to understand what aspects of the roadmap are changing and which remain unchanged.

Constraints:
- Maintain a professional yet conversational tone.
- Avoid assigning blame to the vendor or any team members; use neutral, forward-looking language.
- Clearly state the 3-week delay and acknowledge the vendor delay factually.
- Mention the mitigation plan is underway but details are pending.
- Emphasize transparency about what is changing and what stays the same.
- Keep the email concise and focused.

Output format:
- A complete email text suitable for internal team communication.

Examples:
- "Due to a vendor delay, our Q3 roadmap timeline will shift by approximately three weeks."
- "We are actively working on a mitigation plan to address this delay; I will share details once finalized."
- "Key deliverables scheduled for Q3 will be adjusted accordingly, while some milestones remain on track."

Success criteria:
- The email clearly communicates the 3-week delay and its cause without blaming anyone.
- The tone is professional but not overly formal or stiff.
- The message includes mention of a mitigation plan with pending details.
- The team understands what changes and what stays the same in the roadmap.